        "created_at": "2019-11-30T20:11:04.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I buy Jouan\u2019s village wines in damn near every vintage - and the Chambolle-Musigny has been a constant.  We had the '09 on Thanksgiving and it was in prime shape.  A good friend is the local importer, and I tend to purchase the off vintage wines for half price to help him turn the product, and Jouan really shines in off vintages.  The '04s right now are superb.</p>",
